Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by E Oelofse] </F>
  [Text] Johannesburg March 24 SAPA -- A live television 
debate between State President F W de Klerk and African National 
Congress [ANC] President Nelson Mandela will be screened on TV 1 
and CCV on Thursday, April 14. On March 28, Minister of Foreign 
Affairs Pik Botha and ANC National Chairman Thabo Mbeki will 
have their turn, on TV 1 only. An SABC [South African 
Broadcasting Corporation] statement on Thursday said the 
moderators for both debates will be SABC political correspondent 
Mr Lester Venter and Radio Metro's Mr Tim Modise. A panel of 
four journalists will put questions to the politicians. 

